    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold an urgent public inquiry into the Family Courts and Cafcass",
        "additional_details": "The APPG on Domestic Violence report shows that nearly 70% of family and Cafcass cases involve domestic abuse yet most remain UNTRAINED.\r\n\r\nEmploying highly trained people like Independent Domestic Violence Advisors is VITAL to advise the courts on cases involving domestic abuse & the safeguarding of children YET this isn\u2019t done\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s NOT about stopping contact it\u2019s about safeguarding children with SUITABLE contact per case.\r\n\r\n123 MPs have called for this yet still the government WONT act. Childrens' lives have already been lost. Please sign so no more unsafe contact is granted\r\n",
        "background": "Abusive parents have been granted access to children against the child\u2019s wishes and feelings. \r\n\r\nChildren can be at risk every contact session as courts have decided \u201ccontact at all costs\u201d as more important.\r\n\r\n",
